9
00:00:48,260 --> 00:00:49,760
It was the first month in the Year of the Red Rooster.

10
00:00:50,470 --> 00:00:51,680
That winter,

11
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:55,190
especially cruel chills swept through our land.

12
00:00:56,350 --> 00:00:58,360
A biting wind trailed us that day.

13
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:01,860
The King left the Palace, dressed in a military uniform,

14
00:01:02,690 --> 00:01:04,900
because our enemy had gotten close to our capital...

15
00:01:05,320 --> 00:01:07,950
and our capital was expected to be seized.

16
00:01:09,450 --> 00:01:12,790
This was a royal flight of the King.

17
00:01:27,220 --> 00:01:30,260
However, our enemy's pursuit was relentless.

18
00:01:31,260 --> 00:01:35,230
The King's safety was as fragile as the candle flame before the wind.

19
00:01:36,390 --> 00:01:37,480
In this predicament,

20
00:01:38,020 --> 00:01:40,020
a military officer stepped forward.

21
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,529
Your Majesty.

22
00:01:44,530 --> 00:01:45,939
I am Guard Chun Geum Hwi of the Royal Guard Command.

23
00:01:45,940 --> 00:01:47,240
Please allow me to speak.

24
00:01:47,820 --> 00:01:49,359
There is a village a day's journey to the south.

25
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:50,950
It is called Yongdam Village.

26
00:01:51,830 --> 00:01:53,490
It is my hometown.

27
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:56,199
It is known as the village where dragons ascend to the sky.

28
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,709
With tall mountains surrounding the village,

29
00:01:57,710 --> 00:01:59,790
the village offers a perfect refuge.

30
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,460
Yongdam Village.

31
00:02:05,550 --> 00:02:07,920
Yes. I must go there.

32
00:02:13,470 --> 00:02:14,560
Halt!

33
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:16,680
Easy.

34
00:02:19,060 --> 00:02:22,019
Your Majesty. I beg you to seek shelter this instant.

35
00:02:22,020 --> 00:02:24,820
The enemy is camped out at the foot of Mount Paltae.

36
00:02:27,690 --> 00:02:30,199
Your Majesty, Mount Paltae stands...

37
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:32,280
to the north of Yongdam Village, does it not?

38
00:02:32,370 --> 00:02:33,489
That is correct.

39
00:02:33,490 --> 00:02:36,620
It appears they have figured out our route.

40
00:02:36,910 --> 00:02:38,620
We must change our direction.

41
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,080
But...

42
00:02:40,420 --> 00:02:43,460
where could we possibly go when we have come this far?

43
00:02:44,340 --> 00:02:47,260
Where must I go to save my life?

44
00:02:47,420 --> 00:02:50,549
We must make haste and find a route heading south.

45
00:02:50,550 --> 00:02:51,679
Say that I do.

46
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:54,100
But what if they follow us? What will I do then?

47
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:57,640
Yes.

48
00:02:59,230 --> 00:03:00,520
Send someone...

49
00:03:00,810 --> 00:03:03,400
to hoist the ceremonial flags high over Yongdam Village.

50
00:03:03,770 --> 00:03:07,280
So the enemy thinks that I am heading to that village.

51
00:03:07,690 --> 00:03:09,439
This ruse should give me a chance...

52
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:11,070
to slip away unnoticed.

53
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:12,280
Yes, Your Majesty.

54
00:03:12,490 --> 00:03:15,120
That is a brilliant idea. We ought to do exactly that.

55
00:03:17,490 --> 00:03:19,250
Please reconsider, Your Majesty.

56
00:03:19,330 --> 00:03:22,370
This trickery will put the people of Yongdam Village in danger.

57
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:25,590
Please allow me two hours.

58
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:27,669
I will have them evacuate the village.

59
00:03:27,670 --> 00:03:29,800
Please give me your permission to do so.

60
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,090
You brainless fool.

61
00:03:31,630 --> 00:03:32,969
If they evacuate,

62
00:03:32,970 --> 00:03:35,260
the enemy will get wind of our plan.

63
00:03:36,470 --> 00:03:39,470
A noble cause demands sacrifice.

64
00:03:40,140 --> 00:03:41,270
Your Majesty.

65
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:43,560
My elderly mother and young son...

66
00:03:43,650 --> 00:03:46,980
live in Yongdam Village.

67
00:03:47,270 --> 00:03:48,650
Please...

68
00:04:02,910 --> 00:04:04,710
Give him a good beating and tie him up,

69
00:04:05,790 --> 00:04:07,500
so he cannot ruin our plan.

70
00:04:08,130 --> 00:04:09,130
Let us go.

71
00:04:38,660 --> 00:04:40,240
- Run! - Over there.

72
00:04:42,830 --> 00:04:43,960
That night,

73
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:45,960
we lived on,

74
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,130
but they perished in our place.

75
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:51,460
How shall we atone...

76
00:04:53,090 --> 00:04:54,380
for this cruel sin?

77
00:04:57,090 --> 00:04:59,640
(Episode 13)

78
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,190
Is everything written in this book...

79
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,980
true?

80
00:05:12,030 --> 00:05:13,650
Did Yeonjong the Great...

81
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:16,700
sacrifice everyone in this village...

82
00:05:17,570 --> 00:05:20,780
to flee from the enemy?

83
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:29,170
So this man named Chun Geum Hwi...

84
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:33,420
harbored deep-rooted resentment toward the royal family,

85
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,720
became the Eight-feet Spirit,

86
00:05:37,970 --> 00:05:39,299
and sought revenge against the royal family.

87
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:40,390
Your Majesty.

88
00:05:41,430 --> 00:05:43,059
My great-great-grandfather,

89
00:05:43,060 --> 00:05:46,390
in his folly, left behind records of the royal family's shameful act.

90
00:05:46,810 --> 00:05:48,480
I will not seek...

91
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:53,940
your forgiveness regarding my ancestor's disrespect.

92
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:59,200
Your punishment will be decided in due time.

93
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:02,160
You are dismissed.

94
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:03,620
Yes, Your Majesty.

95
